{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 How We Score Senior Housing Facilities\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 How We Score Senior Housing Facilities\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Each facility receives a composite quality score from 0 to 100, built from six categories. A score of 50 represents \u8220"meets the standard\u8221" \u8211- not average among peers, but an absolute baseline. When a category has no available data, its weight redistributes proportionally across the remaining categories. A facility needs at least three scored categories to receive a composite score.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Regulatory (30% of composite)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Regulatory is the single heaviest category because it directly reflects resident safety.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 We pull DSHS inspection reports \u8211- the actual PDF documents from state inspections \u8211- and use AI to evaluate two dimensions per report: how severe were the violations found (event score), and how well did the facility respond (response score). Each report gets scored on both dimensions, then the per-report scores are averaged across all available reports.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The violation severity carries 60% of the weight within this category, the response quality 40%. A facility with clean inspections and no violations scores near the top. A facility with severe or life-threatening violations scores near the bottom regardless of how well they responded afterward.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b High score (80-95):} No violations or only minor ones, with good corrective responses. {\b Low score (0-30):} Severe or life-threatening violations, poor response quality.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Reviews (25% of composite)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Customer satisfaction signal drawn from Google Reviews. Three factors contribute:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Star rating} (the dominant factor): A facility\u8217's Google rating mapped to an 80-point scale. A 5-star facility gets the full 80 points; a 1-star facility gets zero.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Review volume} (up to 10 bonus points): A logarithmic bonus that rewards having more reviews, with diminishing returns. Going from 1 to 10 reviews matters more than going from 90 to 100.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Review recency} (up to 5 bonus points): A small bonus for facilities that are actively accumulating new reviews in the last 24 months.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The star rating dominates because it\u8217's the strongest signal of resident/family satisfaction. Volume and recency are smaller bonuses that add confidence to the rating.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b High score (75-95):} 4.5+ stars with 100+ reviews, many recent. {\b Low score (0-30):} Below 2.5 stars, few reviews.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 Property (15% of composite)\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A proxy for physical facility quality, based on the county assessor\u8217's assessed property value compared to the county median.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A facility assessed at exactly the county median scores 50. A facility at twice the median scores 100. Below the median, the score drops proportionally. The idea: higher assessed values generally correlate with newer construction, better maintenance, or larger/better-equipped buildings.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This is the simplest category right now \u8211- just one data point. Future versions may incorporate building age, improvement-to-land ratios, and other property quality signals.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b High score (75+):} Assessed value 1.5x or more above the county median. {\b Mid score (50):} Right at the county median. {\b Low score (0-25):} Well below the county median.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
